  "prompt": "How do I write a program that calculates a ball's bounce, where the bounce is .6 of its height and user can input initial height and number of bounces (Python)?",
  "response": "You can write a Python program to calculate a ball's bounce height by following these steps:\n\n1. Prompt the user for the initial height of the ball.\n2. Prompt the user for the number of bounces.\n3. Define the bounce factor (0.6 in this case).\n4. Calculate the bounce height after each bounce.\n5. Display the results.\n\nHere\u2019s an example implementation:\n\n```python\ndef calculate_bounce(initial_height, num_bounces, bounce_factor=0.6):\n    bounce_heights = []\n    current_height = initial_height\n\n    for bounce in range(num_bounces):\n        current_height *= bounce_factor  # Calculate the height after the bounce\n        bounce_heights.append(current_height)\n\n    return bounce_heights\n\n\ndef main():\n    # Get user input\n    initial_height = float(input(\"Enter the initial height of the ball (in meters): \"))\n    num_bounces = int(input(\"Enter the number of bounces: \"))\n\n    # Calculate bounce heights\n    bounce_heights = calculate_bounce(initial_height, num_bounces)\n\n    # Display results\n    print(\"\\nBounce Heights:\")\n    for i, height in enumerate(bounce_heights, start=1):\n        print(f\"Bounce {i}: {height:.2f} meters\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n```\n\n### How It Works:\n1. **`calculate_bounce` Function**:\n   - Takes the initial height, number of bounces, and bounce factor as inputs.\n   - Iterates through the number of bounces, calculating the height after each bounce.\n   - Stores the bounce heights in a list and returns it.\n\n2. Main Program:\n   - Prompts the user for the initial height and number of bounces.\n   - Calls the `calculate_bounce` function to compute the bounce heights.\n   - Displays the results in a readable format.\n\n### Example Output:\n```\nEnter the initial height of the ball (in meters): 10\nEnter the number of bounces: 3\n\nBounce Heights:\nBounce 1: 6.00 meters\nBounce 2: 3.60 meters\nBounce 3: 2.16 meters\n```\n\nThis program calculates and displays the height of the ball after each bounce based on the user\u2019s input.",
